<subSubSection id="BEC36531FFCAFFC56CEEFE3344F1374D" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F66636BAFFCAFFC56CEEFE3344F1374D" blockId="30.[151,1436,464,635]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="C4ADEAA8FFCAFFC56CEEFE3347103738" bold="true" box="[199,322,500,526]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Prothorax wider than long; sides gradually widening from anterolatero angles to apex of lateral tubercles, which are acute and slightly directed backward; elytra without centrobasal crest; metafemora not surpassing elytral apex in male; femora clavate; metatarsomere I often longer than II and III together. See diagnois of 
<taxonomicName id="31D94D39FFCAFFC5691EFDFB46EC374C" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anisopodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C4ADEAA8FFCAFFC5691EFDFB46EC374C" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Anisopodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Number of species currently included: 15.
</paragraph>
